rComments: AVOID AT ALL COSTS. Absolutely horrible professor. Difficult to understand and terrible at explaining. Reads off powerpoints that are confusing and finishes lectures early and just ends it. To explain questions he writes on a slant in paint. Completely illegible. Quizzes can have trick questions, be prepared to answer things he never taught. BEWARE

Avoid if you can. The content on quizzes and tests however, is quite fair but he gives very little time to do them (10 mins per quiz and 60 mins per midterm). His examples in class are quite hard to follow as he writes on a 90 degree angle for some reason. Thankfully the course follows the textbook and there are resources online to self teach.

During the class, he would use less 1h to read the slides and then wait for your question. If there is no question, class dismissed. He always records the class but never upload it. Exams are really heavy if you don't read the book carefully, he will turn a programming class into a concept recitation class. If the class is not mandatory, just run!

If you really to to waste your time, you must take this professor class. He won't let you pass unless you are willing to be tortured. This professor even does not know what he is talk about, he will use 1 hour to read the ppt and just hold the zoom session and doing nothing for 2 hours. nothing you can learn and ridiculous assignment feedback

Lots of quizzes (eg. quiz on new material 2 days before midterm). Does not compromise (eg. refuses students asking for more time on tests). However, he is accessible outside of class, most quizzes had above a passing average, and you get bonus marks for participating in polls during held during lectures. Keep up with the lectures and you will pass.

This would have to be one of the worst profs I have ever encounter in all of my academia. He is not here for you. He is here to read the slideshow and yell at you for asking any questions. He does several quizzes that have too many questions for only 10 minutes. I would avoid him at all costs.

This guy is just awful. Lectures are dry and boring, but the material is not difficult, and easy enough to learn on your own time. However, the evaluation method for this course is absurd. Grades are based off of quizzes, a midterm and a final. However, not nearly enough time is allocated for these tests, making them far more difficult than needed.

Very dry lectures where he definitely has trouble explaining how concepts work. Somewhat confusing and slow speaking pattern. He prefers to show the method rather than explain it. He does a lot of reading off the slides when it would be beneficial really to do examples instead. AVOID this guy if you can.
AVOID HIM. HE MADE LECTURES SO BORING. 3-hours lectures usually end within 1 hour. very few practice questions were provided and exams were out of content

Doesn't care about students at all. No office hours, no TAs - says office hours are during his class.
